        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48450",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Why should the validate method being extended?\r\nThere is no benefit in having this additional informations, and sorting them internally.\r\nThe validator looks only if there is ONE matching record. For the match itself it is useless if there is a sorting or not.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-15T20:54:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-09-15T20:54:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48454",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=romac",
                        "name": "romac",
                        "displayName": "Rob McClean",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "1. Why should the validate method being extended?\r\nAre you're asking why I'm extending it? Well, I have a very specific reason - it's because it nearly does what I want! What I want to do is, after calling isValid(), grab a copy of the MX Hosts array to use in the next stage of a process.\r\n2. There is no benefit in having this additional informations, and sorting them internally.\r\nOK, OK, not for you! But either make the function protected so I can override it and do what I wish, or expose that array, correctly sorted by weight.\r\n3.The validator looks only if there is ONE matching record. For the match itself it is useless if there is a sorting or not.\r\nAgreed, for the match itself. (But the sort takes less time than the call to getmxrr() - I can post that code if you wish) And, hey, I'm suggesting promoting it to be protected function. You could add a parameter to the signature to choose between 'exists' and 'sorted list' without breaking anything.\r\nRegards\r\nRomac\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=romac",
                        "name": "romac",
                        "displayName": "Rob McClean",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-16T09:29:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-09-16T09:29:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48455",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Nope, I did not disagree to make it protected nor did I ask why you want to extend it.\r\nBut I asked why additional informations should be taken in account in the existing validation when they are not used internally.\r\nI see no reason to extend the implementation, get informations which are not used and store them internally so that others can extend the class based on not used informations.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-16T12:22:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-09-16T12:25:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48458",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=romac",
                        "name": "romac",
                        "displayName": "Rob McClean",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "OK, no problem, thanks. It was just an idea. (p.s. I'm a newbie to Zend and this Issue tracker. Sorry if I've commented inappropriately)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=romac",
